---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
	<main>
    <div class="background-icon-container">
      <object data="/icon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" width="200">
        <img src="/web-app-manifest-512x512.png" />
      </object>
    </div>
		<h1><span class="text-gradient">Privacy Policy</span></h1>

    <section>
      <p>At Aglow, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, share, and protect your information when you use our social media app.</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect various types of information to provide and improve our services, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> When you sign up, we may collect information like your name, email address, phone number, and profile photo.</li>
        <li><strong>Content and Activity:</strong> We collect the content you create and share on Aglow, such as posts, comments, and interactions with other users.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We gather information about how you use the app, including features accessed, settings chosen, and other engagement metrics.</li>
        <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We may collect details about your device, including IP address, operating system, and device model, to help improve performance and security.</li>
        <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> With your permission, we may access your location to provide location-based features.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>Aglow uses your information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide and personalize our services based on your preferences and activities.</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about updates, new features, and promotional offers.</li>
        <li>Analyze usage trends to improve app functionality and user experience.</li>
        <li>Detect, prevent, and address security or technical issues.</li>
        <li>Enforce our Terms of Service and protect the safety of our users and community.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Anonymization and Non-Sale of Contact Information</h2>
      <p>To safeguard your privacy, any contact information you share with us is anonymized for security purposes. We do not sell your personal information, including anonymized contact details, to third parties.</p>

      <h2>4. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information in the following cases:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> We may share your information with third parties if you have given your explicit consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We work with third-party vendors who help us operate, maintain, and improve the app. These providers have limited access to your information and are bound by privacy agreements.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).</li>
        <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> If Aglow is involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, your information may be transferred as part of the transaction.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
      <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain your personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy or as required by law. When no longer needed, your data will be securely deleted or anonymized.</p>

      <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>Aglow is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we learn that we have collected information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete it promptly.</p>

      <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update our Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of significant updates through the app or by email. Continued use of Aglow after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

      <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at support@aglow.com.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1rem;
		width: 800px;
		max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
		color: white;
		font-size: 20px;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
  .background-icon-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
	.astro-a {
		position: absolute;
		top: -32px;
		left: 50%;
		transform: translatex(-50%);
		width: 220px;
		height: auto;
		z-index: -1;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 4rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}
	.text-gradient {
		background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-size: 400%;
		background-position: 0%;
	}
	section {
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	h2 {
		font-size: 1.8rem;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
	}
</style>
